{{see|Monopoly}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
'''Mo-no*po-ly'''
{{rfp}}

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[monopolia]]'', from Greek ''[[monopolion]]'', from ''mon'' + ''polein'', to [[sell]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A situation where there is [[only]] [[one]] [[company]] is [[provide|providing]] a certain [[product]] or [[service]].  The company gets to [[choose]] the [[price]] it wants.

